caption:
Want to help create a more inclusive UW tech community? 🌟 Looking to join a fun, welcoming team? 🎉 Great news—our Fall 2024 Tech+ Organizing Team applications are now open! 📢

Check the link in our bio 🔗 for available roles and become a part of the Tech+ family 🌱

At Tech+, we're all about fostering diversity, equity, and inclusion in the tech space. 🌍 Our mission is to make tech accessible to all students, regardless of their background or previous experience. We prioritize growth, learning about underrepresented communities in tech, and providing valuable resources. 📚

Students from ALL faculties and programs are welcome to apply! 🎓 No prior tech experience is necessary 😊

APPLY BY AUGUST 4th @ 11:59 PM!!! ⏰🌱🌱
accessibility_caption: Photo by Tech+ UW 🌱 on July 31, 2024. May be a graphic of poster and text.

caption:
🌟✨ Fascinating Friday Feature! ✨🌟

While TikTok may joke about finding a man in finance, we at Hera.co are celebrating the women. This week, we spotlight Muriel Siebert—the first woman to buy a seat on the NYSE and the first female superintendent of banking in New York. Her groundbreaking achievements paved the way for gender equity in finance, inspiring future generations of women to shatter glass ceilings and demand equal opportunities. 💼💪

🔗 Dive into the link in our bio to learn more about Siebert’s legacy. 📖 #FascinatingFriday #WomenEmpowerment

caption:
‼️Applications Extended ‼️

❓Missed out on your opportunity to apply for the CSC Organizing Committee? Fear not as the deadline has been extended until August 3rd! 🎉

📣 Being apart of the UW Computer Science Club organizing committee comes with many perks where you can gain valuable skills in leadership and teamwork while contributing to one of the largest clubs at the University of Waterloo! You will have opportunities to connect and support fellow computer science interested students here at UW (and across the globe 🌎)

🎯 We aim to bring the computer science community closer together, and strengthen both their academic and professional skills… but we can’t do it without you on our team!

📖 We welcome everyone from ALL faculties, including incoming first years! Most of our roles do not require ANY computer science experience or knowledge!

👀 More information and application can be found in the link in our bio!

⏲️  The form will close on August 3rd at 11:59 PM EDT (UTC-4), so apply ASAP! We'll reach out through email after this date for interviews.

👉 Alternatively, you can email us at exec@csclub.uwaterloo.ca from your UW email with an introduction of yourself, which positions you're interested in, and any questions you might have.
